  DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN

    The xxcclloocckk(1X11R5) program displays the time in analog or digital form.
    The time is continuously updated at a frequency that can be specified by
    the user. This program is nothing more than a wrapper around the Athena
    Clock widget.

  OOPPTTIIOONNSS

    The xxcclloocckk(1X11R5) utility accepts all of the standard X Toolkit command-
    line options, along with the additional following options:

    --hheellpp
        This option indicates that a brief summary of the allowed options
        should be printed on the standard error.

    --aannaalloogg
        This option indicates that a conventional 12-hour clock face with tick
        marks and hands should be used. This is the default. If both --aannaalloogg
        and --ddiiggiittaall are specified, the last one on the command line takes
        effect.

    --cchhiimmee
        This option indicates that the clock should chime once on the half
        hour and twice on the hour.

    --ddiiggiittaall
        This option indicates that a 24-hour digital clock should be used. If
        both --aannaalloogg and --ddiiggiittaall are specified, the last one on the command
        line takes effect.
    --hhdd color
        This option specifies the color of the hands on an analog clock. The
        default is bbllaacckk.
    --hhll color
        This option specifies the color of the edges of the hands on an analog
        clock, and is only useful on color displays. The default is bbllaacckk.
    --ppaaddddiinngg number
        This option specifies the width in pixels of the padding between the
        window border and clock text or picture. The default is 10 on a
        digital clock and 8 on an analog clock.
    --uuppddaattee seconds
        This option specifies the frequency in seconds at which xxcclloocckk(1X11R5)
        should update its display. If the clock is obscured and then exposed,
        it will be updated immediately. A value of less than 30 seconds will
        enable a second hand on an analog clock. The default is 60 seconds.

  XX DDEEFFAAUULLTTSS

    This program uses the Athena Clock widget. It understands all of the core
    resource names and classes as well as the following:
    wwiiddtthh (classWWiiddtthh)
        Specifies the width of the clock. The default for analog clocks is 164
        pixels; the default for digital clocks is whatever is needed to hold
        the clock when displayed in the chosen font.
    hheeiigghhtt (class HHeeiigghhtt)
        Specifies the height of the clock. The default for analog clocks is
        164 pixels; the default for digital clocks is whatever is needed to
        hold the clock when displayed in the chosen font.
    uuppddaattee (class IInntteerrvvaall)
        Specifies the frequency in seconds at which the time should be
        redisplayed.
    ffoorreeggrroouunndd (class FFoorreeggrroouunndd)
        Specifies the color for the tic marks. The default is depends on
        whether reverseVideo is specified. If reverseVideo is specified the
        default is llwwhhiittee; otherwise the default is bbllaacckk.
    hhaannddss (class FFoorreeggrroouunndd)
        Specifies the color of the insides of the clock's hands. The default
        is depends on whether reverseVideo is specified. If reverseVideo is
        specified the default is llwwhhiittee; otherwise the default is bbllaacckk.
    hhiigghhlliigghhtt (class FFoorreeggrroouunndd)
        Specifies the color used to highlight the clock's hands. The default
        depends on whether reverseVideo is specified. If reverseVideo is
        specified the default is llwwhhiittee; otherwise the default is bbllaacckk.
    aannaalloogg (class BBoooolleeaann)
        Specifies whether or not an analog clock should be used instead of a
        digital one. The default is True.
    cchhiimmee (class BBoooolleeaann)
        Specifies whether a bell should be rung on the hour and half hour.
    ppaaddddiinngg (classMMaarrggiinn)
        Specifies the amount of internal padding in pixels to be used. The
        default is 8.
    ffoonntt (classFFoonntt)
        Specifies the font to be used for the digital clock. Note that
        variable width fonts currently will not always display correctly.

